      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne, ¶ 22 Dec. 1891. ¶ T. R. Wilson Esqr ¶ Under Secretary. ¶ Sir....</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">91.12.22</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Thomas Wilson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">R91/11797, unit 645, VPRS 3992/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department. Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">22 Dec. 1891.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">T. R. Wilson Esqr</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Under Secretary.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the honor to solicit, that authority may be granted for the payment of £21.12/.-, by which amount I now find the authority S. 2772 is exceeded for the printing-payment of the new edition of the "Select plants". By some oversight, which I hope will be excused, I thought the payment would simply be by the sheets; but I see now, that in my letter of the 4th April 1891<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The estimate in M to T. Wilson, 4 April 1891was for '1000 copies of about 560 pages', 16 pages to a sheet; the published version has 594 pages plus a one page postscript.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I estimated the work to comprise<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">about</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>35 sheets, whereas it really became extended to 38 sheets, so that yet payment for these three sheets at £7.4/-<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>each has to be rendered, by £21.12/-<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Fund for this is available under the item "publication of work" in the Gov. Botanists establishment. I may add, that nearly the whole cost of the work will be regained for the revenue,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>as the book sells well.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Chief Secretary, A. McLean, minuted his approval on 24 December. On 8 January 1892,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>G. Bell, for the Under Secretary, forwarded the news to M who returned the file 'with best thanks' on 12 January. The file was then forwarded to the Commissioners of Audit.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir, your obedient servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Gov. Botanist.</p>
         </div>
